There has been an increase in overall temperatures throughout the NES ecosystem during the handcast timeseries, but the overall increase is small (+0.017C per year), though significant (p<1e-10). The linear fit shows that year accounts for only 13% of the variation seen. This is expected, as SST is a complex function with many covariates.
